          <declname>alloc</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Returns the total number of bytes allocated by a memory allocator, or 0 if the allocator does not track memory usage. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Note that because of allocation overhead, the total size MAY be larger than the sum of the sizes specified to <ref refid="memory_8h_1a90830d17a2e79efd7d376803588fad48" kindref="member">mem_alloc()</ref>. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
